Re: i'm possibly switching to linux, which should i get?
by thedotmaster on Fri Sep 12, 2008 3:32 pm	([msg=11508]see Re: i'm possibly switching to linux, which should i get?[/msg])
Best thing about Linux is that because it is free, you can chop and change.Start with Ubuntu, then perhaps try Mandriva, Xandros etc. Just look around for the one you like the best.Most Linux distros are around 500mb-1gb.As for "Microsofty", all Linux systems have the same basis so whatever they look like - start menu etc - they are still Linux.Basically, you just want to learn UNIX.
