by thedotmaster on Wed Sep 02, 2009 9:14 pm	([msg=28982]see Re: i'm possibly switching to linux, which should i get?[/msg])
JakeMS wrote:GNU is Not Unix.GNU/Linux and UNIX are two completely different things. Unix is basically Mac, GNU/Linux is.. well the Linux kernel.Same as BSD is not Linux, it's BSD again, different.Heh, yes, I am aware. However, UNIX does not just define code but defines practices and standards.People say "Learn UNIX" to mean learn about how *nix systems work, learn the command line, etc.Unix, however, is not "basically Mac". Mac is built on the BSD kernel.
